1️⃣ Activity Diagram: Inventory Reorder Process

Purpose:
Shows how the system automatically reorders stock when inventory is low.

Activities & Flow
(Start)
   ↓
Check Stock Level
   ↓
[Decision] Stock Below Threshold?
   ├── No → Continue Monitoring → (End)
   └── Yes
        ↓
Generate Purchase Order
        ↓
Send Order to Supplier
        ↓
Receive Order Confirmation
        ↓
Update Inventory Status
        ↓
(End)

Key UML Elements

Initial Node: Start

Decision Node: Stock Below Threshold?

Final Node: End

Control Flows: Arrows between activities

2️⃣ Activity Diagram: Sales Processing Workflow

Purpose:
Represents the workflow from receiving a customer order to completing the sale.

Activities & Flow
(Start)
   ↓
Receive Sales Order
   ↓
Validate Stock Availability
   ↓
[Decision] Stock Available?
   ├── No → Display Out of Stock Message → (End)
   └── Yes
        ↓
Process Sale
        ↓
Update Inventory
        ↓
Generate Invoice
        ↓
(End)

Key UML Elements

Decision Node: Stock Available?

Alternative Flow: Out-of-stock handling

Final State: Sale completed or terminated
